               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18370918-2254-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-2254-18370918 t18370918-2254-offence-1 t18370918-2254-verdict-2"></join>
               <p>2254. <persName id="def1-2254-18370918" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2254-18370918" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2254-18370918" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2254-18370918" type="surname" value="M'KEW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2254-18370918" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MICHAEL M'KEW</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-2254-18370918" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-2254-18370918" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2254-18370918" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2254-18370918" type="surname" value="FLOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-2254-18370918" type="given" value="SILVESTER"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">SILVESTER FLOOD</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18370918-2254-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2254-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2254-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> stealing, on the <rs id="t18370918-cd-192" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370918-2254-offence-1 t18370918-cd-192"></join>8th of September</rs>, 117 yards of bed-tick, value 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18370918-name-1251" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1251" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1251" type="surname" value="DICKENSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1251" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370918-2254-offence-1 t18370918-name-1251"></join>William Dickenson</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1252" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1252" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1252" type="surname" value="TIDMARSH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1252" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES TIDMARSH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. In consequence of information I received from Williams on the 8th of September, I watched a house in the Maze, at South walk, from half-past nine o'clock till about half-past eleven at night, when I saw two men come out—we let them pass us, and a third person came out, which was M'Kew—we took him into custody, and went into the house, and found this property in a room there—the other two men did not answer the description we had received of the men—Flood was one of those two.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1253" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1253" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1253" type="surname" value="WILLIAMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1253" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD WILLIAMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a steam-boiler-maker, and live in Queen street, King-street, Borough. On the 8th of September, between nine and ten o'clock, I saw two men and a woman come from under an arch of London-bridge—M'Kew was one of them—he had a parcel on his shoulder—I followed them down to the church, in Tooley-street, and lost sight of them by the side of the rail-road—I gave information to the officer—the paper round the parcel was torn, and I could see by the gaslight that it was bed-ticking—I cannot speak to Flood—he wore a cap similar to the other man, but I thought the man was shorter than him. <hi rend="smallCaps">SUSANNAH MULHEEN</hi>. One Catherine Flood lodged with me in the Maze. On the 8th of September, about ten o'clock, the prisoners came to the house—the woman was out at the time—when she came in she saw bundle when she went up stairs, and she said to the prisoners, "Who brought it here? it will do none of us any good, take it out, or I will throw it into the cart-road"—M*Kew had brought it in—I did not hear them make her any answer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">M'Kew</hi>, The other man was coming along, and picked it up—being rather tired, he asked me to carry it, and I did, and the policeman caught me at the corner of the court.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1254" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1254" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1254" type="surname" value="'"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1254" type="given" value="WILLIAM DICKENSON"></interp>WILLIAM DICKENSON. '</persName>
                  </hi> I have not the least doubt of this bed tick being my property—I sent a quantity of bed-tick to a wharf, on Friday the 8th of September, on the Southwark side of London-bridge, very near the arch—it was worth 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.,—this is the quantity within two yards, and the package is the same—it has the direction on it which mine had, and the man who packed it is here.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1255" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1255" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1255" type="surname" value="WARREN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1255" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE WARREN</persName>
                  </hi>. I packed up this bed-tick—the direction is my writing—it belongs to Mr. Dickenson.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1256" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1256" type="surname" value="HOLMES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1256" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HOLMES</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in White's-alley, Coleman-street. I carried the parcel to the wharf, and left it at the wrong wharf—I think I left it is the care of Flood, but I am not certain—it was to go to Canterbury. <hi rend="italic">Flood</hi>. I am sure I did not receive it from him or any man—I picked it up in the street.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1257" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1257" type="surname" value="HAVILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1257" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HAVILL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 2.) I found the parcel at Mulheen's house, in the back room, first floor—it was cut up into thirteen pieces, and this paper with the direction on it was with it—part of the property had a strap round it—in carrying it to the station-house flood said</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183709180193"></xptr>
               <p>he found it near Fenning's wharf, and acknowledged the strap to be his—I had seen the prisoners come out of the house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">M'Kew</hi>. I delivered it at a house, by Flood's desire, and immediately I came down the officer collared me. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. We heard them tearing it up as we were standing outside the house—they were there two hours before they come out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MRS. MULHEEN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. They were in the house from ten o'clock till the officer took them—I was at home took them—I was not present when they tore the stuff up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">FLOOD</hi>. I was at home and in bed when I was taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1258" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1258" type="surname" value="HAVILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1258" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HAVILL</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. We allowed him to pass, not suspecting him—I had seen him before, and thought him a hard working man—I apprehended him in bed in Bull-court.(Flood received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">M'KEW</hi>—<hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18370918-2254-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-2254-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-2254-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 18.—
<rs id="t18370918-2254-punishment-200" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2254-punishment-200" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
